y tested sample codes  and videos While the projects are electronics based the bulk of his work is rooted in industrial engineering  Middleton is managing quality control and working with manufacturers and vendors  the operations  and working with people  how long this is going to take for them to make them  and the price margins  I feel like I was applying a lot of the things I learned in the classes at UIC  Quintin L  Williams Jr  a clinical assistant professor in the Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering at UIC  He approaches his education with a very calculated and strategic methodology  Always sitting in the front row and freely participates in class  Brady is a true innovator Having a diverse engineering background is one of the key factors that allowed Middleton to coordinate the elements of starting and operating a business  Otherwise  he would have to hire people  which would affect his bottom line  He credits the industrial design program with preparing him for this venture  we take electrical engineering class Apart from the curriculum  Middleton uses the vast resources UIC provides  He has been working at mHUB  which is an innovation center for product development and manufacturing  Through UIC  he was able to get an associate membership and work in their space mHUB  the setting  and everybody is moving and working and it makes you want to work harder  We can do so much more here and UIC provides a lot for us  the Makerspace  and the CAD Lab  UIC has already fostered this environment and the students just need to do it  For me Learn more about Think    at https   www think    com uic edu ie program https   www think    com http   mie uic edu ie program By David Staudacher  UIC By David Staudacher  UIC  n nFacebook n  n nTwitter n  n nGoogle Plus n  n nLinkedin n  n nTumblr n  n nEmail n   You may also like  n  Congratulations to Don McLauchlan  n   n   n  r n     Engineering Research Facility  r n    W  Taylor Street r nChicago  IL        r